column1: Conjunto Topo Chico - Pedro, Tomas Y Jose - ACME Records AC-001-A,"Title: Pedro, Tomas Y Jose
column3: Accompaniment: Acordeón, Bajo Sexto Y Contrabajo
column7: Notes: Matrix number in shelac reads: AC-001-A.  This corrido takes place at around 5pm and is about 2 rivals named Tomas and Pedro.  Pedro pulled out a gun and killed Tomas, a friend went to Tomas’ house to tell his father what had happened.  The father Jose,  went to take revenge.  The Jose ended up shooting Pedro.  When the authorities came, Jose the father willingly went to jail because he took revenge for killing his sons murderer.

column3: Accompaniment: Acordeón, Bajo Sexto Y Contrabajo
column7: Notes: Matrix number in shelac reads: AC-002-B.  This is a farewell from a man who is going to prison.  He killed a man for trying to steal his woman, who eventually left him.  It mentions he will be put to death by “La Silla”, or the electric chair.

column1: Conjunto Topo Chico - Higinio Adame - ACME Records AC-003-A,"Title: Higinio Adame
column3: Accompaniment: Acordeón, Bajo Sexto Y Contrabajo
column7: Notes: Matrix number in shelac reads: AC-003-A.  This corrido takes place on a Friday in 1951.  Higinio Adame was drinking at the Cantina Hernandez looking to have a good time.  Higinio ask the waitress for a beer, the waitress replied yes but you have to go to a different table.  Guicho started heckling Higinio until Higinio could not take it any more and began to fight with Guicho, during the fight Guicho got stabbed.  Higinio ended up getting forty years in in prison for this crime.

column1: Hermanos Saenz  - Corrido De Alonso - Aero 110-B,Title: Corrido De Alonso
column3: Accompaniment: con Accordeon y Bajo Sexto
column7: Notes: Loud surface noise due to wear.  This corrido is about about Alonzo who took revenge for his father.  Corrido starts out with Alonzo going to Texas with his mother and then returning to to Mexico to take revenge for his father.  Alonzo killed a military leader named Margarito who it turns out  would take money from the store owners.
